Anteater Chess - Final Release
ChessEaters, EECS 22L, UC Irvine
April 2026
Version 1.0

Authors: Collan Harrington, Claire Nguyen, Jordan Le, Tara Pai, Yanilette Montano, Aurea Jolly

Anteater Chess is a modified version of chess played on a 10x8 board with two extra
pieces called Anteaters. The goal is to checkmate the opponent's king.

Extra features:
  - Three AI difficulty levels: Easy, Medium, Hard
  - Human vs Human mode
  - Computer vs Computer (AI vs AI) mode
  - Chess clock (per-player timer)
  - Undo last move button

To install, type "make". For detailed instructions see INSTALL.
For how to play, refer to doc/Chess_UserManual.pdf.
